annotationA: HL01743p; Phosphatidate phosphatase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: thermotaxis; dephosphorylation; response to light intensity; phototransduction
annotationB: Sphingosine-1-phosphate lyase; Cleaves phosphorylated sphingoid bases (PSBs), such as sphingosine-1-phosphate, into fatty aldehydes and phosphoethanolamine. Sphingolipid catabolism is required for normal development including viability, reproduction and muscle development; Belongs to the group II decarboxylase family. Sphingosine-1-phosphate lyase subfamily
